			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Blasting is a process of reducing a solid body, such as rock, to fragments by using an explosive. It involves drilling holes, placing a charge and detonator in each hole, detonating the charge, and clearing away the broken material. The process is efficient, economical, and fast, and is widely used for removing rust and heat-treat scale. Safety in blasting involves assessing, controlling, monitoring, and managing risk throughout the entire process.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">爆破是使用炸药将岩石等固体物质炸成碎片的过程。它包括钻孔、在每个孔中放置装药和雷管、引爆装药并清除碎料。该工艺高效、经济、快速，广泛用于除锈和热处理水垢。爆破安全涉及整个过程中的风险评估、控制、监测和管理。</common:generalComment>
